algorithm: The new algorithm calculates the score for each bin by taking the product of the square root of the reciprocal of the remaining capacity divided by the maximum capacity, the logarithm of the item size divided by the maximum capacity, and the reciprocal of the square of the minimum remaining capacity divided by the maximum capacity, then subtracting the natural logarithm of the item size divided by the square root of the maximum capacity, finally divided by the logarithm of the maximum capacity divided by the square root of the item size.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    log_item = np.log(item)
    sqrt_max_cap = np.sqrt(max_capacity)
    sqrt_min_cap = np.sqrt(np.min(bins))

    scores = np.sqrt(1 / (bins / max_capacity)) * (log_item / max_capacity) * (1 / (sqrt_min_cap**2 / max_capacity)) - log_item / (sqrt_max_cap / np.sqrt(item))

    return scores
